Economies of scale 
is the ability to reduce costs and gain effciency when operating at a larger scale 

Capital Expenditure (CapEx) 
is the upfront spending of money on physical infrasture, and then deducting that upfront expense over time

Oprational Expenditure (OpEx)
There is no upfront cost, as you pay for a service or product as you use it 

consumption 
based model - allows end - users only pay for the resources that they use 


